<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">
<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/Forum75/HTML/000145.html">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#400000"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#400000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Dave</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">When i used to play UO. Which will be the very type of people playing AC.  I strated off as a newbie. like everyone else.  I ran to the graveyards first to see what went on there.  And watched guild wars go on.  People would come back to their guild armmed for the next fight.  Lone warriors would run in quickly taking sides and adding to the blood shed.  Screams filled my screen.  People cast spells back and forth.  They would run to their slain enemy and take the sword of force they saw earlier in his hand, then turn it against their foe.  When it all ended, the same ammount of people and items left the graveyard.  When an item is looted somone is happy and somone might be frustrated.  By it being deleted or left on a lost corpse, one person is sad, and the computer is happy, which is imposible, violence adds a new area for roleplay of evil charcters, and good charcters to act out their good deeds.  the game was more fun this way.  If players wanted to save money witha  no-pvp game they could just by a one player game.  Without pvp thats all the game is, NPC killing with a chat room</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Joe Napalm</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans"><BR>I've stood up for PvP many times, but there is a lot more to AC than a single player game with a chat-room, even if they scrapped PvP altoghether.<P>The focus of AC is multi-player. A lot of people get more enjoyment out of a game if they can play with their friends - even if they can't kill one another. The most fun I've had in AC is in fellowships, fighting back-to-back against hordes of AI nasties. Would I have had even more fun if those opponents had been other players? Maybe...maybe not. But I still had a lot more fun than I would have had in a single player game.<P>-Jn-</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Havoc_3D</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Although i am somewhat of a PK lover (blood Thirsy,what can i say) I think they should keep PK down, i do like the idea of some type of team PvP, like a Guild war and such,i think open PK should be left out.  It seems that open PK causes big problems for the low lvl newbies,ppl take advantage of it and just have newbie kill fests,i think PKing is a good thing,but only in a controlled limited scence.  As a reply to the last post, I agree,it is very fun to fight back to back with comrades against a horde of baddies,but that can still be accomplished in a team pvp environment.<P>                -Havoc_3D</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Aspasia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">I've Given The PvP Mess A Lot Of Thought Lately Due To The Fact That I've Been Getting Slightly Annoyed With People In Dereth. Also, When You Can't Lay A Hand On Someone, Even As A Joke (Haven't We All Wanted To Slap Our Friends Upside The Head For A Point Of Damage or Two For A Laugh?) It Takes Some Realism Out Of The Gameplay. There Are A Lot Of Ideas Out There To Work Through This, Most of Them Need Too Much Game-Changing Work To Be Done, Though. My Favorite Idea Would Be To Have The Switch In Your Settings... This Makes You Available To Be Hit By Other Players And To Hit Other Players That Are Willing To Be Hit. This Could Be Coupled With A System That Would Include Duels And Wars. There Could Be Some Code Added For You To Make A List (Like A Friends List) Of Persons You Can Fight With. This Would Make For Friendly Sparring, Heated Duels, And If You Want To be That Organized - Guild Wars. Plus, You Could Reach Over And Knife Your Friend Who Happened To Leave The Computer To Find His Notebook Full Of AC Notes..... Anyway, I'd Like To See Something Done About It. The Way We Have It Set Now Just Doesn't Seem To Fit In With The Mentality Of Most Of The People. You Don't Have To be Evil To Be A PKer... You Just Have To Be Good (At It) <BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</IFRAME>
</FONT>
